p: Flow cytometry analysis demonstrated that cell populations derived from SPFP were entirely or partly positive for the MSCs, mean surface immunophenotype expression value were showed as CD29 = 92.30 ± 3.20%, CD73 = 90.91± 2.73%, and CD105 = 83.52 ± 3.23% ( Figure 2A–C). Moreover, cell populations showed lacked surface expression of hematopoietic stem cell markers CD 34 = 1.04 ± 2.88% and CD45 = 0.92 ± 1.08% ( Figure 2D,E).
